Defendant Adam R Merkel in court with attorney Andrew Charles Ladd.  Timothy Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin. State moved to dismiss count 1 and moved to strike the repeater allegation in counts 2 through 4. Court grants, dismissed count 1 and dismissed the repeater allegation in counts 2 through 4.

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Counts 2, 3 and 4

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

COUNT 2: 9 MONTHS STRAIGHT TIME; CREDIT - 7 days;

COUNT 3: 90 DAYS STRAIGHT TIME, CONCURRENT TO COUNT 2

COUNT 4: 9 MONTHS STRAIGHT TIME, CONCURRENT TO COUNTS 2 AND 3


TERM OF PROBATION: 18 MONTHS; each count (2, 3 & 4) concurrent;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*Absolute Sobriety;  
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling; 
*No violent contact with wife or any family member;  
*Anger Management or Domestic Violence counsling - whatever agent deemed appropriate.

RESTITUTION:  $0

COURT COSTS:  $343.00 count 2 (includes $100.00 DV surcharge) and $243.00 each for counts 3 and 4. Apply cash bail, refund balance.

CONDITION TIME: 30 days Huber STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.   
